<sections.12>
C
n summary, this article has focused on the clinical approach to ischemic stroke, intracerebral intraparenchymal hemorrhagic stroke, a. SAH, ruptured intracranial aneurysms, and unruptured intracranial aneurysms. Important details in the diagnosis and management of these conditions were presented in order to stimulate further discussion with colleagues in neurology and neurosurgery so as to develop rational treatment plans.
